						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the ruined temple of Lakshmīnārāyanasvāmi.</p>						

						<p>Kākatīya: Rudradēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1189, Prabhava, Vaiśākha śu. 13, Saturday, corresponding to 1267 A.D., April 8.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to register a gift of land by Dēvaparāja of Tāḍlapalli, the <hi rend="italic">Pradhāni</hi> of Jannigadēva, who was the minister of the king, for conducting worship to an image of Lakshmīnārāyaṇa in the village. Further it records the gift of some tolls and mentions Aṁbusamudram and Kāchasamudram.</p>						

						</summary>
